textAfterTable: Player Details Will Grigg is a young striker with Walsall. He progressed through the club's youth ranks and made his first-team debut when coming on as a substitute against Cheltenham in December 2008.  Will signed a professional contract for the Saddlers in the summer of 2009 but it was not until the 2010-11 campaign that he broke into the first-team squad on a regular basis.  He featured in over half the club?s League One fixtures, scoring four goals, including his first ever in senior football in the 2-2 draw with Bristol Rovers in January.
